synthbio.models
Class Circuit

java.lang.Object
  synthbio.models.Circuit
All Implemented Interfaces:
JSONString
public class Circuit
extends Object
implements JSONString

Circuit representation. A Circuit is defined by a name, description and three lists: Gates, input proteins and output proteins. Circuits' fromJSON is guaranteed to return a valid circuit. When constructing the Circuit manually, a validate() method is supplied to check validity.

Author:
jieter

addSimulationInput

public void addSimulationInput(String p,
                               String input)
Add the simulator input 'input' for protein 'p'. If the input string does not span the simulation length, the last tick is repeated for the rest of the simulation length.

Parameters:
p - Protein
input - Input string consisting of (H|L) for each tick.

validateProteins

public void validateProteins()
                      throws CircuitException
Validate the use of proteins in the circuit. If the circuit is valid, no exception is thrown. Could be done in a more efficient manner, but for the time being this is straightforward and explicit.

Throws:
CircuitException - if some error is found in the protein assignment.
